THOUGHT: The verifier crash happens because DeadArgumentElimination changes function signatures or return values in the presence of musttail calls, violating musttail invariants (exact return type match and immediate ret). Although there is some propagation for musttail callers, it only propagates from already-live functions. To be safe, we should conservatively mark both functions that contain musttail calls and their callees as live upfront, preventing any signature or return transformation on them. I will modify DeadArgumentElimination.cpp to add an initial scan that marks such functions (and their direct musttail callees) live before any deletions or liveness computations.

```bash
applypatch << 'EOF'
*** Begin Patch
*** Update File: llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/DeadArgumentElimination.cpp
@@
 PreservedAnalyses DeadArgumentEliminationPass::run(Module &M,
                                                    ModuleAnalysisManager &) {
   bool Changed = false;

+  // Conservatively mark functions involved with musttail calls as live to avoid
+  // changing their signatures or return values, which would violate musttail
+  // invariants (exact type match and immediate ret after the call).
+  // This includes any function that contains a musttail call and the direct
+  // callee of that musttail call.
+  for (Function &F : M) {
+    for (BasicBlock &BB : F) {
+      for (Instruction &I : BB) {
+        if (auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(&I)) {
+          if (CB->isMustTailCall()) {
+            markLive(F);
+            if (Function *CalleeF = CB->getCalledFunction())
+              markLive(*CalleeF);
+          }
+        }
+      }
+    }
+  }
+
   // First pass: Do a simple check to see if any functions can have their "..."
   // removed.  We can do this if they never call va_start.  This loop cannot be
   // fused with the next loop, because deleting a function invalidates
   // information computed while surveying other functions.
   LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "DeadArgumentEliminationPass - Deleting dead varargs\n");
*** End Patch
EOF
```

